The paper proposes a model for human activity recognition using multimodal sensor data. The model uses parallel recurrent neural networks with convolutional attentions to select the most salient features adaptively. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, machine learning and computer vision are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on developing a model for activity recognition using sensor data.
